PROCESS TO HOST A WEBSITE
STEP 1> INSTALL HTTP SERVICE
      #yum install httpd -y
STEP2>START AND ENABLE HTTPD
      #systemctl start httpd
      #systemctl enable httpd
STEP 3> CHANGE DIRECTORY AND MOVE TO HTML DIRECTORY
      #cd /var/www/html
STEP 4> CREATE AN INDEX.HTML FILE ADD CONTENT IN IT
      #vim index.html{file name will be always index.html}
      WRITE- <h1> welcome to httpd </h1>
STEP 5> ADD PORT FOR HTTP SERVICE
      # firewall-cmd --add-port=80/tcp --permanent
      #firewall-cmd --reload
STEP 6>SEE WEBSITE IS CREATED 
      #curl localhost/ip of machine
STEP7> OPEN A BROWSER AND WRITE LOCALHOST U WILL SEE THE INDEX.HTML FILE CONTENT       
